modules.description: This module implements connection establishment with Happy Eyeballs algorithm variations, handling concurrent IPv4 and IPv6 connection attempts with configurable delays and timeouts. It works with domain names, IP addresses, and socket file descriptors, providing functions to connect to hosts or pre-resolved IP addresses. Concrete use cases include robust client connection logic for network applications like HTTP clients or peer-to-peer systems, where fast fallback between IP versions is required.
